</i></p><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-14_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">In today's competitive business environment, marketing is more crucial than ever. It is not just about promoting products or services but about creating value and building relationships with customers. This is where the Chartered Institute of Marketing (CIM) comes into play. CIM is a professional body dedicated to supporting and developing marketers, ensuring they adhere to high standards and contribute effectively to their organisations. In this blog, Dr Richard Dune explores the role of CIM, key facts and statistics, and the best practices for implementing relevant legislation and regulations.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Previous" class="pf-slider-prev none hide"></button><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Next" class="pf-slider-next none hide"></button></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-0d47" data-category="Collection Suggestion" data-name="Tea" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-kYHfwS doYKjf pf-16_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-hAcGzb cVhebe"><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-17_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-18_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-19_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key facts and statistics</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-21_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Marketing professionals are the backbone of any successful business. According to the Marketing Week Career and Salary Survey 2023, the average salary for a marketing professional in the UK is £45,000, highlighting the value and importance of skilled marketers. CIM plays a pivotal role in shaping these professionals, with over 30,000 members globally, demonstrating its extensive reach and influence in the marketing sector.






























</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-23_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-24_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-25_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-27_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-28_ pf-text-1"><strong>Chartered Institute of Marketing (CIM)</strong> - CIM is the world's largest professional marketing body. It provides a range of qualifications, training, and resources to support marketers at all stages of their careers. CIM's mission is to create marketing advantage for the benefit of professionals, businesses, and society.


</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-30_ pf-text-1"><strong>Marketing standards</strong> - CIM has established a framework that defines the skills and knowledge required for effective marketing practice. These standards ensure marketers are equipped with the latest industry insights and best practices.
</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-32_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-33_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-34_ pf-heading-1-h3">Best practices for implementing relevant legislation and regulations
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-36_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Marketing is subject to various legislation and regulations designed to protect consumers and ensure fair competition. Implementing these effectively is crucial for maintaining trust and avoiding legal repercussions. Here are some recommended best practices:































</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-38_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Data protection and privacy</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-40_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">With the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) in effect, marketers must prioritise data protection and privacy. This involves obtaining explicit consent from individuals before collecting their data, ensuring data is stored securely, and being transparent about how data is used. Regular training and updates on GDPR compliance should be a part of any marketing team's routine.































</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-42_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Advertising standards</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-44_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Adhering to the Advertising Standards Authority (ASA) guidelines ensures all marketing communications are legal, decent, honest, and truthful. Marketers should be familiar with the ASA's codes and regularly review their compliance campaigns.































</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-46_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Consumer protection</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-48_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Marketers must comply with the Consumer Protection from Unfair Trading Regulations 2008, prohibiting misleading actions and omissions. Ensuring all claims are substantiated and transparent is key to maintaining consumer trust and avoiding legal issues.
































</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-50_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-51_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-52_ pf-heading-1-h3">The role of CIM in promoting best practices
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-54_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">CIM supports marketers in navigating these complex regulatory landscapes through its comprehensive resources, training, and professional development opportunities.

































</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-56_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-57_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-58_ pf-heading-1-h3">Training and qualifications
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-60_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">CIM offers a range of qualifications, from foundation to postgraduate levels, ensuring marketers have the knowledge and skills needed to excel in their roles. These qualifications are designed to be relevant and practical, providing insights into the latest marketing trends and regulatory requirements.


































</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-62_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-63_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-64_ pf-heading-1-h3">Continuous Professional Development (CPD)
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-66_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">CIM's CPD programme encourages marketers to update their skills and knowledge continually. This is particularly important in a field as dynamic as marketing, where regulations and best practices constantly evolve.


































